```json
{
  "application": "COBALT",
  "details": {
    "scheduler": "COBALT",
    "runtime": 60,
    "nodes": 1,
    "output_directory": "/home/vsastry/$COBALT_JOBID",
    "conda_environment": "/lus/theta-fs0/projects/datascience/vsastry/Benchmarks/Pilot1/Uno/uno_conda_env",
    "python_version": "python --version",
    "openmp_threads": 64,
    "script": "uno_to_tfrecords.py",
    "data_source": "all",
    "cache_directory": "./cache/all",
    "h5_path": "/grand/projects/datascience/memani/uno-dataset/All.h5",
    "batch_size": 4096,
    "tfrecords_directory": "all_TFR"
  }
}
```

This script runs on the **COBALT** workload manager, a resource management system for high-performance computing clusters. It uses a conda environment for managing dependencies. The script utilizes the `uno_to_tfrecords.py` script for converting data to TFRecords format. It also utilizes specific resources like the `$COBALT_JOBID` environment variable,  `$COBALT_NODEFILE`, and `OMP_NUM_THREADS` for managing the execution environment. The script reads data from a specific H5 file located at `/grand/projects/datascience/memani/uno-dataset/All.h5` and creates TFRecords in a directory called "all_TFR".
